Just Don't Blame The Parents For ADHD... I have an urge to write when I am triggered by something that angers me. Last weekend, after a hard exercise session, over a congratulatory coffee in the cafe for surviving the hour, I had a conversation that left me with a sense of disquiet all week. Author, Counsellor, Lifespan Integration Therapist, Supervisor & trainer.

What Questions Should Parents Really Ask On A School Visit? Most parents spend months, if not years, deciding which school is right for their children. This is why a school visit is so important and why parents should spend time thinking about the questions they want to ask, which in my experience can be broken down into two categories. Assistant Director of Education for Cognita Schools. Previously at Wakefield City Academies Trust. Worked in education all my life.

The Big Little Sister To Syd, Brody is Brody. She accepts him for who is he - her brother. And in a world where we really should just embrace differences and celebrate them, that's a beautiful thing. Because sadly this isn't always the case. Mother. Blogger. Campaigner

Mothering The Mother - The Key To Raising Breastfeeding Rates? Mothering the mother is a phrase often heard during pregnancy and birth. Look after the mother, care for her, support her emotional needs ... and she will feel more empowered to grow, birth and care for her baby. A phrase (and actions) that makes so much sense and is seen in many cultures across the world. Associate Professor in Child Public Health at Swansea University, UK

