Getting To Grips With The 'Normal' Birth Debate One argument seems to be that it makes some women feel abnormal if they don't give birth naturally. Given the statistics, this would make the majority of UK mothers 'abnormal'. The term 'normal' is not a judgement on an individual, but a statement of physiological fact about a particular bodily process. Professor in midwifery studies at the University of Central Lancashire (UCLan)

