-Title- 
Tory Rebels Hopeful Government Will Use Budget To Reveal Universal Credit Concessions
-Keywords-
['labour', 'hopeful', 'tory', 'rebels', 'told', 'universal', 'wollaston', 'vote', 'concessions', 'reveal', 'sixweek', 'secretary', 'budget', 'credit']
-SUMMARY ARTICLE-
Tory rebel MPs who raised fears Universal Credit roll-out could plunge working families into poverty are hoping the government will reveal some concessions in next month’s budget.
We have heard many compelling cases today and we cannot ignore them.”PA Archive/PA Images Totnes MP Sarah Wollaston was the only Tory to vote against the government.
